title: Argentina celebrates World Cup victory
description: Fans go wild after Argentina claimed the World Cup title following an exciting final match in Doha. The team beat France in a penalty shootout. Lionel Messi led his team to victory, nabbing the first World Cup trophy in his career.

title: Pope Francis wrote resignation note after 2013 election in case of health impediment
description: Pope Francis revealed that after being elected pontiff  he wrote a resignation letter in case medical problems impede him from carrying out duties.

title: Deadly unrest leaves American tourists stranded in Machu Picchu
description: Deadly protests in the wake of a political crisis has left a number of American tourists stranded in and around Peru's Machu Picchu.

title: What could GOP control of the House mean for U.S.-China tensions?
description: Congressional Republicans have vowed to get tougher on China as they take control of the House, raising concern that ties could be further destabilized.

title: Croatia beats Morocco 2-1 to take 3rd place at World Cup
description: Croatia ended up taking third place at the World Cup after a 2-1 win over Morocco at Khalifa International Stadium on Saturday.

title: Israel deports Palestinian activist to France
description: Israel said it deported a Palestinian lawyer and activist to France early Sunday, claiming he has ties to a banned militant group, despite Paris' objections.

title: Poland’s top cop accidentally set off grenade launcher gifted by Ukraine
description: Poland’s top police official told a radio broadcaster that a grenade launcher that was a present from Ukrainian officials accidentally exploded in his office.

title: North Korea fires 2 ballistic missiles in resumption of testing
description: North Korea fired a pair of ballistic missiles on Sunday toward its eastern waters, its first weapons test in a month.

title: Death toll rises to 24 in Malaysia campsite landslide; 9 remain missing
description: Rescuers on Saturday found the bodies of a woman and two children, raising the death toll from a landslide on an unlicensed campground in Malaysia to 24.
